    "intended": "Let $f(n)$ be minimal such that, for any $A=\\{a_1,\\ldots,a_n\\}\\subseteq [2,\\infty)\\cap\\mathbb{N}$ of size $n$, in any interval $I$ of $f(n)\\max(A)$ consecutive integers there exist distinct $x_1,\\ldots,x_n\\in I$ such that $a_i\\mid x_i$.\n\nObtain good bounds for $f(n)$, or even an asymptotic formula.",
